<body>
    <h1>AIP Sentinel Automation Framework Documentation</h1>
    
    <h2>1. Overview</h2>
    <p>The <strong>AIP Sentinel Test Automation Framework</strong> is a robust, scalable, and highly maintainable end-to-end framework built leveraging modern automation standards. It is constructed using <strong>WebdriverIO (v9.x)</strong> with <strong>TypeScript</strong>, utilizing the <strong>Mocha</strong> testing framework for a behavior-driven development (BDD) style approach.</p>
    <p>The framework supports cross-layer testing, seamlessly combining Frontend UI Automation via WebdriverIO with Backend API validations using <code>axios</code> to ensure comprehensive data integrity across the platform.</p>

    <h2>2. Architecture & Tech Stack</h2>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Component</th><th>Technology / Tool</th></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Core Language</strong></td><td>TypeScript</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Test Runner</strong></td><td>WebdriverIO (WDIO)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Test Framework</strong></td><td>Mocha JS</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Design Pattern</strong></td><td>Page Object Model (POM)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>API Testing</strong></td><td>Axios (HTTP client)</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Visual Regression</strong></td><td><code>@wdio/visual-service</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>Reporting</strong></td><td>Allure Reporter & JUnit</td></tr>
        <tr><td><strong>CI/CD</strong></td><td>Jenkins</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>3. Architecture Components</h2>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Test Specifications (<code>test/specs/</code>)</strong>: Contains logical test case sequences. Consumes page objects and test data.</li>
        <li><strong>Page Objects (<code>test/pageobjects/</code>)</strong>: Contains UI select locators and action methods for reusability.</li>
        <li><strong>Test Data & Utils (<code>test/utils/</code>)</strong>: Feeds dynamic data configurations into specs.</li>
        <li><strong>Web Browser Engine</strong>: Google Chrome executes UI instructions.</li>
        <li><strong>API Client</strong>: Axios makes direct backend system state validations alongside UI steps.</li>
        <li><strong>Reporters</strong>: Generates Allure HTML Dashboard and JUnit XML files for Jenkins.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Framework Directory Structure</h2>
    <pre>
├── .github/                 # GitHub specific rules
├── TestResults/             # Output artifacts
│   ├── allure-results/      # Raw JSON data for Allure
│   ├── junit/               # JUnit XML reports for Jenkins
│   └── logs/                # Framework execution logs
├── test/
│   ├── pageobjects/         # Page Elements and Action Methods
│   ├── specs/               # E2E Test Scenarios
│   └── utils/               # Configurations & dynamic test data
├── wdio.conf.ts             # Master WebdriverIO Configuration
├── package.json             # NPM dependencies & scripts
├── Jenkinsfile              # Jenkins CI/CD Pipeline
└── run-test.cjs             # Standalone runner
    </pre>

    <h2>5. Execution Commands</h2>
    <p>The framework integrates seamlessly with NPM scripts for easy execution.</p>
    
    <h3>Prerequisites</h3>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Node.js</strong> Version <code>22.18.0</code> or higher</li>
        <li><strong>NPM</strong> (Node Package Manager)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Installation</h3>
    <pre>npm install</pre>

    <h3>Running Tests</h3>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Purpose</th><th>Execution Command</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Run the complete test suite</td><td><code>npm run wdio</code> (or <code>npm run test</code>)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Run a specific test</td><td><code>npx wdio run ./wdio.conf.ts --spec test/specs/Apps_test.e2e.ts</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Run tests headless (CI)</td><td>Handled automatically in Jenkins or via <code>--headless=new</code> flag</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h3>Generating Reports</h3>
    <table>
        <tr><th>Purpose</th><th>Execution Command</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Create and open Allure Report</td><td><code>npm run report:allure</code></td></tr>
        <tr><td>Clear old test reports</td><td><code>npm run allure:clear</code></td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>6. Key Features & Workflows</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Integrated E2E and API Validations:</strong> Tests interact with the UI, parse table data, and query APIs simultaneously to ensure the database matches the frontend.</li>
        <li><strong>Dynamic Test Data Injection:</strong> Test credentials and logic are maintained in <code>dynamicTestData.ts</code> and <code>testdata.json</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Automated Error Logging:</strong> Whenever a test fails, it auto-captures screenshots and directly attaches them into the Allure Report.</li>
        <li><strong>Visual Testing:</strong> Powered by <code>@wdio/visual-service</code> to pinpoint visual pixel regressions.</li>
    </ol>
</body>
</html>
